The paper deals with automated inference on criminality using face images, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the ethical implications of such research, which is relevant to computer ethics (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms to make predictions about individuals based on their physical appearance also falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data mining techniques to extract information from large datasets, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
